Netwrix Enterprise Auditor v11.6 > Solutions > Exchange Solution > 8.Exchange Online Job Group > Mailflow Job Group > EX_Mailflow_DL Job
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Solutions/Exchange/Online/Mailflow/EX_Mailflow_DL.htm
 

What software is currently installed?
Could we get the text output (copy&past) from the following ADMIN PowerShell ISE script block on the systems that are running Netwrix/Stealth Server applications?

Clear-Host  # Clears the console window for better readability. 
#Netwrix/Stealth, PostgreSQL, Python application versions:
Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Product |
Where-Object {($_.Name -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.Name -like "Netwrix*" -or $_.Name -like "*Postg*" -or ` $_.Name -like "Python*")} -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
Sort-Object | Format-Table Name,Version,InstallDate -AutoSize 

#Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) formally StealthAUDIT (SA) install path
$env:SAINSTALLDIR 

#Netwrix Access Information Center (AIC) formally StealthAUDIT Access Information Center (AIC) install path
(Get-ItemProperty -Path "HKLM:SYSTEMCurrentControlSetServicesAccessInformationCenter"-ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).ImagePath.Replace("`"", "").Replace("BinAccessInformationCenter.Service.exe", "")

TextBody:
Lenny,

Thank You for the update, I will look over the logs we collected.

Please let me know how the next set of job runs complete.

  The build of PowerShell should not matter to our application as long as it is installed.

Per our call today we confirmed that the current version of Stealth application(s) running in the Environment:

Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) 11.6.0.89    << Recommend patching to the lasted build 

We found the following error preventing the collection job from updated needed details 
'Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.PowerShellGet.Telemetry' error: Unable to find type [Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.PowerShellGet.Telemetry].

Checked the following via PowerShell 
Get-ExecutionPolicy -List                                                                  <<<  Us Unrestricted     
Get-Module -ListAvailable ExchangeOnlineManagement               <<<  Listed Version 3.2.0 
Get-Module -ListAvailable Microsoft.Graph                                    <<<  Returned no entries, however we see within the C:Program FilesWindowsPowerShellModules
Get-Module -ListAvailable Azure*                                                   <<<  Returned no entries 

This lead us to find the needed Prerequisites to use Modern Authentication for Exchange Online in Enterprise Auditor (Exchange Online Management v3.4.0) was missing.
Netwrix Enterprise Auditor v11.6 > Requirements > Exchange Solution > Target Exchange Online Requirements, Permissions, and Ports > Exchange Online Auditing Configuration > Prerequisites https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/Config/ExchangeOnline/Access.htm#prerequisites 

We were not able to update as the needed command posted the following:
PackageManagementUninstall-Package : The module 'ExchangeOnlineManagement' of version '3.2.0-Preview3' in module base folder 'C:Program FilesPowerShellModulesExchangeOnlineManagement3.2.0'
was installed without side-by-side version support. Some versions are installed in this module base with side-by-side version support. Uninstall other versions of this module before uninstalling
the most current version.
****NOTE**** This is not the path to the Module we noted the path is C:Program FilesWindowsPowerShellModules
Uninstall-Module -Name ExchangeOnlineManagement -RequiredVersion 3.2.0 
As well as 
Uninstall-Module -Name ExchangeOnlineManagement 
Both failed
Uninstall a module
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/powershellget/uninstall-module?view=powershellget-3.x#example-1-uninstall-a-module 
I was able to run Uninstall-Module -Name ExchangeOnlineManagement -RequiredVersion 3.6.0  in my lab without issue possible this is an issue of how the module was originally installed?
Looks like the following should work as well 
Uninstall-Module -Name ExchangeOnlineManagement -AllVersions
Uninstall-Module -Name Microsoft.Graph -AllVersions
Uninstall-Module -Name AzureAD -AllVersions 

From there we should be able to run 
# The following will install the most current Version(s) 
Install-Module Microsoft.Graph
Install-Module ExchangeOnlineManagement
Install-Module AzureAD 

REF: Install-Module (PowerShellGet) - PowerShell | Microsoft Learn
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/powershellget/install-module?view=powershellget-3.x

Lenny,

Per our call today we confirmed that there is data in the Netwrix Access Analyzer (NAA) formally Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) formally StealthAUDIT (SA) EX_Mailflow_DL tables (SA_EX_MailFlow_DL_AzureMemberCount & SA_EX_MailFlow_DLsByCount)

Looking at the data within SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) for the ReceivedCount we switched this to DESC from asc

Populating the SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last30days_EXO and SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO tables.
EXAMPLE:
IF EXISTS (SELECT * FROM sys.objects WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID(N'[dbo].[SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]') AND type in (N'U'))
  DROP TABLE [SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]

SELECT
            DISTINCT RecipientAddress AS RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment as DL,
            ISNULL(COUNT(*),0) AS ReceivedCount
INTO
            SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO
FROM
            SA_EX_MailFlow_History
WHERE
            RecipientType = 'Distribution List' and [Date] > GETDATE()-180  --SAME for the -30 query
GROUP BY
            RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment
            Order by ReceivedCount DESC -- WAS asc

Populating the SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last30days_EXO and SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO tables.
EXAMPLE:
IF EXISTS (SELECT * FROM sys.objects WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID(N'[dbo].[SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]') AND type in (N'U'))
  DROP TABLE [SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]

SELECT
            DISTINCT RecipientAddress AS RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment as DL,
            ISNULL(COUNT(*),0) AS ReceivedCount
INTO
            SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO
FROM
            SA_EX_MailFlow_History
WHERE
            RecipientType = 'Distribution List' and [Date] > GETDATE()-180  --SAME for the -30 query
GROUP BY
            RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment
            Order by ReceivedCount DESC -- WAS asc

Per our call today we confirmed that there is data in the Netwrix Access Analyzer (NAA) formally Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) formally StealthAUDIT (SA) EX_Mailflow_DL tables (SA_EX_MailFlow_DL_AzureMemberCount & SA_EX_MailFlow_DLsByCount)

Looking at the data within SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) for the ReceivedCount we switched this to DESC from asc

Populating the SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last30days_EXO and SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO tables.
EXAMPLE:
IF EXISTS  (SELECT *  FROM sys.objects WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID(N'[dbo].[SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]') AND type  in (N'U'))
  DROP TABLE [SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]

SELECT
            DISTINCT RecipientAddress AS RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment as DL,
            ISNULL(COUNT(*),0) AS ReceivedCount
INTO
            SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO
FROM
            SA_EX_MailFlow_History
WHERE
            RecipientType = 'Distribution List' and [Date] > GETDATE()-180  --SAME for the -30 query
GROUP BY
            RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment
            Order by ReceivedCount DESC -- WAS asc

Per our call today we confirmed that there is data in the Netwrix Access Analyzer (NAA) formally Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) formally StealthAUDIT (SA) EX_Mailflow_DL tables (SA_EX_MailFlow_DL_AzureMemberCount & SA_EX_MailFlow_DLsByCount)

Looking at the data within SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) for the ReceivedCount we switched this to DESC from asc

Populating the SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last30days_EXO and SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO tables.
EXAMPLE:
IF EXISTS (SELECT * FROM sys.objects WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID(N'[dbo].[SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]') AND type in (N'U'))
  DROP TABLE [SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]

SELECT
            DISTINCT RecipientAddress AS RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment as DL,
            ISNULL(COUNT(*),0) AS ReceivedCount
INTO
            SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO
FROM
            SA_EX_MailFlow_History
WHERE
            RecipientType = 'Distribution List' and [Date] > GETDATE()-180  --SAME for the -30 query
GROUP BY
            RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment
            Order by ReceivedCount DESC -- WAS asc

Looking at the data within SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) for the ReceivedCount we switched this to DESC from asc

Populating the SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last30days_EXO and SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO tables.
EXAMPLE:
IF EXISTS  (SELECT *  FROM sys.objects WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID(N'[dbo].[SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]') AND type  in (N'U'))
  DROP TABLE [SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]

SELECT
            DISTINCT RecipientAddress AS RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment as DL,
            ISNULL(COUNT(*),0) AS ReceivedCount
INTO
            SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO
FROM
            SA_EX_MailFlow_History
WHERE
            RecipientType = 'Distribution List' and [Date] > GETDATE()-180  --SAME for the -30 query
GROUP BY
            RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment
            Order by ReceivedCount DESC -- WAS asc

Hey Lenny,

Thank you for meeting with me today. To recap our session:

Let me know how things look once the Mailflow jobs complete in a few hours.

Per our call today we confirmed that there is data in the Netwrix Access Analyzer (NAA) formally Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) formally StealthAUDIT (SA) EX_Mailflow_DL tables (SA_EX_MailFlow_DL_AzureMemberCount & SA_EX_MailFlow_DLsByCount)

Looking at the data within SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) for the ReceivedCount we switched this to DESC from asc

Populating the SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last30days_EXO and SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO tables.
EXAMPLE:
IF EXISTS  (SELECT *  FROM sys.objects WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID(N'[dbo].[SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]') AND type  in (N'U'))
  DROP TABLE [SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]

SELECT
            DISTINCT RecipientAddress AS RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment as DL,
            ISNULL(COUNT(*),0) AS ReceivedCount
INTO
            SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO
FROM
            SA_EX_MailFlow_History
WHERE
            RecipientType = 'Distribution List' and [Date] > GETDATE()-180  --SAME for the -30 query
GROUP BY
            RecipientAddress,
            RecipientDepartment
            Order by ReceivedCount DESC -- WAS asc

IF EXISTS (SELECT * FROM sys.objects WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID(N'[dbo].[SA_RS_DLCountReceived_Last180days_EXO]') AND type in (N'U'))

SELECT

SELECT
